{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9ef83b48-909d-4e35-9d6f-99434d8c528a","content":"The project is small — just one file. Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n\nThis is an untestable static call because you can't control the clock in tests.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `timezone.now()` wrapped behind an injectable dependency, or at minimum use `django.utils.timezone.now()` so you can mock it with [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests you can freeze time easily:\n\n```python\nfrom freezegun import freeze_time\n\n@freeze_time(\"2026-01-01\")\ndef test_index(self):\n    response = self.client.get(\"/\")\n    ...\n```\n\n**Summary:** 1 file scanned, **1 untestable static** found (`datetime.now()`). No other common offenders (`date.today()`, `time.time()`, `random.*`, `uuid4()`, `os.environ`, etc.) were detected.\n\nWant me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9027ccac-3271-42c5-a357-28986f5298b3","outputTokens":301,"requestId":"7C10:203FDB:2CC8964:31D2E33:69F95CE4"},"id":"97b5cc3c-0d8e-4f32-a92b-312c66aa24c8","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:58:53.590Z","parentId":"29a2eb87-956b-4a82-a614-01892db2f3f3"}
